-- Areva, Bongrain, Ciments Francais, LVMH, Pernod: French Equity Preview
-- B y   L a u r e n c e   F r o s t
-- 2010-11-08T05:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-07/areva-eiffage-lvmh-pernod-ricard-may-be-active-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual changes in Paris. Symbols are in
parentheses after company names and prices are from the last
close.  France’s CAC 40 Index was little changed at 3,916.73 in
Paris. The  SBF 120 Index  gained less than 0.1 percent.  Areva SA  (CEI FP): Talks on the sale of two EPR nuclear
reactors to India are “very advanced” and may lead to the
signing of a contract during French President Nicolas Sarkozy’s
visit to the country next month, Le Figaro reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer Anne Lauvergeon. The shares fell 2.1
euros, or 0.6 percent, to 347.65 euros.  Bongrain SA  (BH FP): The dairy-products maker said nine-
month sales rose 5.9 percent to 2.554 billion euros. The shares
dropped 1.42 euros, or 2.4 percent, to 57.58 euros.  Ciments Francais SA  (CMA FP): The construction-material
producer posted an 8.1 percent decline in nine-month operating
profit to 662.7 million euros. It forecast lower operating
results in the fourth-quarter. The shares increased 51 cents, or
0.8 percent, to 67.86 euros.  Eiffage SA  (FGR FP): The construction group reported a 2.2
percent increase in third-quarter sales to 3.43 billion euros
and said its order book stood at 9.9 billion euros as of Oct. 1.
The shares rose 68 cents, or 1.8 percent, to 37.845 euros.  LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA  (MC FP): A probe into
the luxury goods group’s purchase of a 17.1 percent stake in
Hermes will focus on whether the dealings were transparent and
whether shareholders were “correctly informed,” Jean-Pierre
Jouyet, the head of France’s market regulator, told Le Journal
du Dimanche. The shares fell 10 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 119.10
euros.  Nexeya  (ALEUR FP): The defense electronics maker fiscal
first-quarter revenue climbed 18 percent to 27.5 million euros.
The shares rose 16 cents, or 1.5 percent, to 10.55 euros.  Pernod-Ricard SA  (RI FP): Groupe Bruxelles Lambert said it
raised its stake in the drinks maker to 9.9 percent. The shares
retreated 1.18 euros, or 1.8 percent, to 63.05 euros.  Securidev SA  (SCDV FP): The security-systems maker said
third-quarter sales fell 0.4 percent to 33.6 million euros. The
shares dropped 52 cents, or 2.1 percent, to 24 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
